1
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:14,608
You have visitors.

2
00:00:14,692 --> 00:00:15,983
I apologize.

3
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:17,608
What the hell do you want?

4
00:00:17,692 --> 00:00:21,775
Please let us accompany you!
At least during the Waves!

5
00:00:21,858 --> 00:00:23,942
[NAOFUMI] Can you arrange
a class upgrade for us?

6
00:00:24,025 --> 00:00:25,150
[SLAVE TRADER]
You can still get it done

7
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,650
by simply applying
at any other country's

8
00:00:27,733 --> 00:00:29,067
dragon hourglass.

9
00:00:29,150 --> 00:00:30,358
[NAOFUMI]
We won't be able to get there

10
00:00:30,442 --> 00:00:32,150
before the next Wave.

11
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:36,317
[RAPHTALIA] Once all the
Waves have been repelled,

12
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:39,483
you'll probably go back--
back to your home world,

13
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:41,483
and I'll never see you again.

14
00:00:43,817 --> 00:00:45,567
[MIRELIA]
The Wave's nearly here.

15
00:00:45,650 --> 00:00:48,150
[exhales] Can we hold it?

16
00:00:59,108 --> 00:01:01,192
It's almost that time.

17
00:01:01,275 --> 00:01:02,567
Along with the potions,

18
00:01:02,650 --> 00:01:05,817
I threw in some leftover
weapons I had laying around.

19
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,733
They'll make for decent backups.

20
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:09,692
[RAPHTALIA]
Thank you so much.

21
00:01:09,775 --> 00:01:11,358
Still, I'm pretty
impressed you were able

22
00:01:11,442 --> 00:01:13,942
to stock up on so much
medicine in so little time.

23
00:01:14,025 --> 00:01:16,108
This still might not be enough.

24
00:01:16,192 --> 00:01:19,358
There's no way we can tell
what'll happen during the Wave.

25
00:01:19,442 --> 00:01:21,817
[ERHARDT laughs]
If you're being that careful,

26
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:23,900
you won't have to worry at all.

27
00:01:23,983 --> 00:01:24,983
[NAOFUMI]
Oh, right.

28
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:26,733
Hold out your hand, Raphtalia.

29
00:01:26,817 --> 00:01:28,108
All right...

30
00:01:29,942 --> 00:01:31,400
Um, what's that?

31
00:01:34,442 --> 00:01:37,400
[NAOFUMI] It's got a spell to
boost your mana generation.

32
00:01:37,483 --> 00:01:39,275
Helluva present for a lady...

33
00:01:39,358 --> 00:01:41,317
Boost my mana generation?

34
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,483
Will it really?!

35
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:43,900
I'm so happy! Thank you!

36
00:01:43,983 --> 00:01:45,400
Huh?

37
00:01:46,983 --> 00:01:50,025
How come she's the only
one who gets a present?

38
00:01:50,108 --> 00:01:52,275
She isn't, check this out.

39
00:01:55,775 --> 00:01:56,900
[FILO gasps]

40
00:01:56,983 --> 00:01:58,400
It'll make your
speed and agility

41
00:01:58,483 --> 00:02:00,233
twice what it was.

42
00:02:00,317 --> 00:02:02,400
It's cute, Filo. You like it?

43
00:02:02,483 --> 00:02:05,358
[FILO]
Do I like it?! Are you kidding?!

44
00:02:05,442 --> 00:02:08,275
Thank you, Master! Yay!

45
00:02:11,108 --> 00:02:12,358
[NAOFUMI]
And a hairpin won't fall off

46
00:02:12,442 --> 00:02:14,317
when you transform.

47
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,358
What's brought on this
accessory-making spree?

48
00:02:16,442 --> 00:02:17,775
Did some rich eccentric
uncle leave you

49
00:02:17,858 --> 00:02:19,858
his fortune or what?

50
00:02:19,942 --> 00:02:22,650
It'll help 'em boost
their stats, that's all.

51
00:02:22,733 --> 00:02:23,900
Right...

52
00:02:23,983 --> 00:02:25,400
[AKE]
The time has come.

53
00:02:30,192 --> 00:02:31,483
Get yourselves
together because

54
00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:33,275
you'll be teleported with me.

55
00:02:33,358 --> 00:02:34,692
Yes, sir!

56
00:02:35,775 --> 00:02:37,817
{\an8}[NAOFUMI]
Okay, It's time.

57
00:02:44,525 --> 00:02:45,692
{\an8}Here we go...

58
00:02:45,775 --> 00:02:47,442
{\an8}Be right back!

59
00:02:47,525 --> 00:02:49,483
{\an8}[chuckles] I'll be
waiting in the shop!

60
00:02:49,567 --> 00:02:51,483
{\an8}You just come back alive!

61
00:04:35,317 --> 00:04:37,608
[ALL panting]

62
00:04:43,442 --> 00:04:45,358
[screaming]

63
00:04:49,775 --> 00:04:52,108
Everyone else in the village
has already evacuated!

64
00:04:52,192 --> 00:04:53,483
Get out of here now!

65
00:04:53,567 --> 00:04:55,692
[VILLAGER 11A]
R-Right! Yes, sir!

66
00:04:56,983 --> 00:04:58,025
I think he's the last one,

67
00:04:58,108 --> 00:05:00,442
so we're done with
the evacuation.

68
00:05:00,525 --> 00:05:02,567
[VOLUNTEER SOLDIER 11A]
It sure took a while.

69
00:05:02,650 --> 00:05:05,733
Maybe we should
getting back to-- Huh?

70
00:05:05,817 --> 00:05:06,858
[VOLUNTEER SOLDIERS gasp]

71
00:05:10,525 --> 00:05:11,483
[NAOFUMI]
Go!

72
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:12,775
Yeah!

73
00:05:18,358 --> 00:05:19,567
What the...?

74
00:05:19,650 --> 00:05:22,233
They took down a lizardman
like it was nothing!

75
00:05:22,317 --> 00:05:25,108
There're still plenty of them.
Keep your eyes peeled.

76
00:05:25,192 --> 00:05:26,275
[VOLUNTEER SOLDIERS]
Got it.

77
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,983
Ha-cha!

78
00:05:34,608 --> 00:05:36,233
How did she do that?!

79
00:05:38,442 --> 00:05:40,900
Thank you very much for your
help in the past, Shield Hero.

80
00:05:40,983 --> 00:05:42,692
I'm indebted to you.

81
00:05:42,775 --> 00:05:44,650
Where do you know her from?

82
00:05:50,692 --> 00:05:52,608
You're that same lady?

83
00:05:54,108 --> 00:05:57,150
Yes indeed. Thanks to you,
I feel much better now.

84
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,858
[OLD WOMAN 6A]
As you can see.

85
00:06:00,942 --> 00:06:03,150
Wow!

86
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:06,525
[OLD WOMAN 6A] Small fry like
these are no match for me.

87
00:06:06,608 --> 00:06:08,067
I swear by these arms,

88
00:06:08,150 --> 00:06:10,192
which fought many
a formidable foe

89
00:06:10,275 --> 00:06:12,317
back when I was an adventurer.

90
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,483
[OLD WOMAN 6A laughs]

91
00:06:13,567 --> 00:06:15,525
[NAOFUMI]
What the hell did I give her?!

92
00:06:15,608 --> 00:06:17,400
[AKE]
Sir Hero!

93
00:06:17,483 --> 00:06:20,025
Sir! All the villagers
have been moved to safety!

94
00:06:20,108 --> 00:06:23,233
That's great.
Now keep the enemy out.

95
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,650
[NAOFUMI]
It's been three whole hours.

96
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:33,358
What are those guys doing?

97
00:06:33,442 --> 00:06:36,608
Sir Hero. You really should go.

98
00:06:36,692 --> 00:06:39,150
We need to put an end
to the Wave quickly.

99
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:41,608
It'll help all the
villagers as well.

100
00:06:41,692 --> 00:06:43,192
I don't know...

101
00:06:43,275 --> 00:06:45,942
Ha! You can leave
the village to lil' ol' me

102
00:06:46,025 --> 00:06:47,692
and these whippersnappers.

103
00:06:47,775 --> 00:06:49,442
I suppose you're right.

104
00:06:49,525 --> 00:06:52,192
Just don't push
your luck, Grandma.

105
00:06:52,275 --> 00:06:54,942
Raphtalia, Filo,
we're outta here.

106
00:06:55,025 --> 00:06:56,483
--[RAPHTALIA] Right.
--[FILO] 'Kay!

107
00:07:11,192 --> 00:07:12,400
Master Naofumi!

108
00:07:12,483 --> 00:07:13,650
Huh?

109
00:07:15,233 --> 00:07:18,108
[FILO]
What a big ship!

110
00:07:19,983 --> 00:07:21,150
[ITSUKI]
Keep it up!

111
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:32,317
[NAOFUMI]
Where are the others?

112
00:07:35,358 --> 00:07:37,442
[ITSUKI]
They're on the ship.

113
00:07:37,525 --> 00:07:38,983
I told them that
attacking that figurehead

114
00:07:39,067 --> 00:07:41,942
and spawning the Soul Eater
came first, but nope...

115
00:07:42,025 --> 00:07:43,983
They won't listen to reason.

116
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:45,192
[ITSUKI gasps]

117
00:07:58,942 --> 00:08:00,275
[yells]

118
00:08:26,858 --> 00:08:29,525
[MOTOYASU panting]

119
00:08:29,608 --> 00:08:31,192
What are you doing, Motoyasu?

120
00:08:31,275 --> 00:08:33,317
We need to take
out the skeleton!

121
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,358
We're gonna have to
take out the kraken first

122
00:08:35,442 --> 00:08:37,525
or the Soul Eater
won't spawn otherwise!

123
00:08:37,608 --> 00:08:38,692
[MYNE]
What are you saying?

124
00:08:38,775 --> 00:08:39,858
[REN'S COMPANION 11A]
You morons...

125
00:08:39,942 --> 00:08:41,942
[NAOFUMI]
This is no time to be bickering!

126
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:46,650
Naofumi...

127
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:49,067
Why don't you go and
defend some village?

128
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:51,650
I agree! An incompetent hero
who can't fight should just--

129
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:53,317
You're the incompetent ones!

130
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,483
[MYNE gasps]

131
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:55,942
Stop wasting time.
If we don't put an end

132
00:08:56,025 --> 00:08:58,525
to the Waves,
more monsters will come.

133
00:08:58,608 --> 00:09:01,608
And I can't do my job! But you--

134
00:09:04,442 --> 00:09:06,108
Instead of working together,

135
00:09:06,192 --> 00:09:08,733
the three of you are
doing whatever you want!

136
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:13,817
If we lose, all the villagers
will die, and so will you!

137
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:17,567
Quit thinking this is some
sort of game, 'cause it's not!

138
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:20,192
[REN] Don't you think
I know that by now?!

139
00:09:20,275 --> 00:09:21,733
That's why I'm
hitting the skeleton

140
00:09:21,817 --> 00:09:22,817
to spawn the Soul Eater!

141
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:24,025
Hah!

142
00:09:24,108 --> 00:09:26,525
You killed it earlier,
but nothing spawned.

143
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:27,858
We have to kill it
more than once

144
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:29,275
to make it work!

145
00:09:29,358 --> 00:09:30,358
I don't believe this...

146
00:09:30,442 --> 00:09:32,233
[REN]
What's that supposed to mean?!

147
00:09:32,317 --> 00:09:33,442
[NAOFUMI]
It doesn't have any special

148
00:09:33,525 --> 00:09:36,108
parameters or resistances.

149
00:09:36,192 --> 00:09:37,608
But there has to
be a way to spawn

150
00:09:37,692 --> 00:09:40,442
a Soul Eater other than
killing that thing.

151
00:09:43,775 --> 00:09:44,942
[NAOFUMI gasps]

152
00:09:45,025 --> 00:09:46,942
[NAOFUMI] Raphtalia!
Cast some light magic!

153
00:09:47,025 --> 00:09:49,067
Light? I can try!

154
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:50,067
Do it!

155
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:51,650
A-All right...!

156
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:54,858
As source of thy power,
I order thee.

157
00:09:54,942 --> 00:10:00,525
Decipher the laws of nature
and illuminate my surroundings.

158
00:10:00,608 --> 00:10:02,567
Fast Light now!

159
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:10,150
Hurry, attack the
shadow at its feet!

160
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:11,275
[RAPHTALIA grunts]

161
00:10:15,942 --> 00:10:17,733
[gasps]

162
00:10:17,817 --> 00:10:19,317
[REN]
Hm?

163
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:20,817
[REN grunts]

164
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,108
[ALL gasp]

165
00:10:24,358 --> 00:10:26,942
Oh, now what are we gonna do?

166
00:10:27,025 --> 00:10:28,025
[ITSUKI]
Look!

167
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:30,567
Soul Eaters are
spawning everywhere--

168
00:10:30,650 --> 00:10:32,192
they're all over the ship!

169
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:54,733
Thunderbolt Slash!

170
00:10:54,817 --> 00:10:56,317
Thunder Arrow!

171
00:10:57,692 --> 00:11:00,192
[MOTOYASU]
Lightning Spear!

172
00:11:05,692 --> 00:11:07,317
It's stronger than I thought.

173
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,692
Are our attacks
even affecting it?

174
00:11:09,775 --> 00:11:13,192
[NAOFUMI] We'll get nowhere
with lightning-element attacks.

175
00:11:13,275 --> 00:11:15,567
Filo! Cast wind magic!

176
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:16,817
'Kay!

177
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,358
Fast Tornado!

178
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:28,525
Come on!

179
00:11:28,608 --> 00:11:30,567
We've got to take it out
before it unleashes that thing!

180
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:31,900
Right with ya!

181
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:37,150
Raphtalia, Filo.

182
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:38,817
Get behind me, quick!

183
00:11:41,067 --> 00:11:43,150
[REN, MOTOYASU scream]

184
00:12:00,733 --> 00:12:02,650
--Filo!
--[FILO] 'Kay.

185
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:04,483
High Quick it is!

186
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:08,567
[FILO grunting]

187
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:11,817
♪ Can't touch me! ♪

188
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,192
[FILO yells]

189
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:22,775
[yells]

190
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:27,192
[FILO grunts]

191
00:12:34,358 --> 00:12:36,817
[NAOFUMI] This strategy
will kill it eventually.

192
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,358
But still...

193
00:12:40,692 --> 00:12:44,275
[NAOFUMI] If we take too long,
the village will be destroyed!

194
00:12:52,483 --> 00:12:54,150
We're not hurting it at all!

195
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:55,442
Stop complaining.

196
00:12:55,525 --> 00:12:56,650
Let's find its weakness.

197
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:57,900
Raphtalia...

198
00:12:57,983 --> 00:12:59,400
What is it?

199
00:12:59,483 --> 00:13:02,150
I'm going to use Rage Shield.

200
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:03,608
Forgive me.

201
00:13:04,692 --> 00:13:06,233
[gasps]

202
00:13:11,108 --> 00:13:13,233
[RAPHTALIA] Don't you
remember what I told you?

203
00:13:13,317 --> 00:13:15,858
You can always count
on me to be your sword.

204
00:13:15,942 --> 00:13:19,150
I will follow you through
fire and brimstone.

205
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:20,942
Never forget it.

206
00:13:24,108 --> 00:13:26,400
Take care of Raphtalia
if anything goes wrong.

207
00:13:26,483 --> 00:13:28,858
[FILO]
Mm-hm!

208
00:13:28,942 --> 00:13:30,275
I'll be here.

209
00:13:30,358 --> 00:13:32,650
By your side until the very end.

210
00:13:38,483 --> 00:13:40,775
[NAOFUMI]
Come forth, Rage Shield!

211
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:51,817
[yells]

212
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:57,108
[ZOMBIE DRAGON]
You will pay...

213
00:13:58,233 --> 00:13:59,525
[NAOFUMI gasps]

214
00:14:04,858 --> 00:14:07,025
[ZOMBIE DRAGON]
You will pay!

215
00:14:12,192 --> 00:14:16,942
[screams]

216
00:14:18,942 --> 00:14:20,525
I don't get it...

217
00:14:20,608 --> 00:14:22,567
[ZOMBIE DRAGON]
For humiliating me,

218
00:14:22,650 --> 00:14:26,192
defeating me as a puny human...

219
00:14:28,483 --> 00:14:29,817
[ZOMBIE DRAGON]
And for humiliating me

220
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:33,858
by taking my bones and
turning me into a tool...

221
00:14:33,942 --> 00:14:35,108
Is that...

222
00:14:35,192 --> 00:14:37,692
Is that the dragon zombie
I absorbed before?

223
00:14:37,775 --> 00:14:40,150
[ZOMBIE DRAGON]
You will pay...

224
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:42,858
You will pay!

225
00:14:45,442 --> 00:14:47,483
What does "Grow up" mean?

226
00:14:53,192 --> 00:14:57,067
[NAOFUMI screams]

227
00:14:57,150 --> 00:15:00,317
[NAOFUMI]
A seething rage...

228
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:03,108
It's not the flame from before.

229
00:15:03,192 --> 00:15:05,025
It's his hatred!

230
00:15:15,942 --> 00:15:20,942
[yells]

231
00:15:21,025 --> 00:15:22,442
What the hell happened to him?

232
00:15:22,525 --> 00:15:23,900
Hey, wait!

233
00:15:27,275 --> 00:15:30,775
Filo's being affected
by the dragon zombie, too?

234
00:15:30,858 --> 00:15:32,150
[FILO yells]

235
00:15:34,608 --> 00:15:40,567
[yelling]

236
00:15:48,483 --> 00:15:50,608
He's basically turned
into a wild beast

237
00:15:50,692 --> 00:15:52,067
and that certainly
isn't how a hero

238
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:53,358
is supposed to fight.

239
00:15:53,442 --> 00:15:55,150
[RAPHTALIA gasps]
What the hell are you people

240
00:15:55,233 --> 00:15:56,817
standing around for?!

241
00:15:56,900 --> 00:15:59,067
Miserable demi-human,
how dare you!

242
00:15:59,150 --> 00:16:00,942
Master Naofumi's
fighting in our place,

243
00:16:01,025 --> 00:16:03,442
doing what we lack
the courage to do!

244
00:16:05,192 --> 00:16:07,358
Yes, it's true.

245
00:16:07,442 --> 00:16:09,983
If only I weren't so useless...

246
00:16:10,067 --> 00:16:13,650
If only I were stronger...

247
00:16:13,733 --> 00:16:16,483
I wouldn't have to
put him through this!

248
00:16:19,067 --> 00:16:20,817
[RAPHTALIA]
You all have the power,

249
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:23,233
so why don't you fight?

250
00:16:23,317 --> 00:16:26,025
How can you call yourself
the world's heroes?!

251
00:16:26,108 --> 00:16:30,067
[NAOFUMI yelling]

252
00:16:30,150 --> 00:16:31,025
[gasps]

253
00:16:31,108 --> 00:16:32,692
Crimson Sword!

254
00:16:35,358 --> 00:16:36,942
[ITSUKI]
Thunder Shot!

255
00:16:42,442 --> 00:16:44,733
Hey, Motoyasu...

256
00:16:44,817 --> 00:16:46,650
Why should I have to
help that bastard?

257
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:48,192
It's not right!

258
00:16:48,275 --> 00:16:51,692
[ITSUKI] I hear you, but we have
no other choice right now.

259
00:16:51,775 --> 00:16:52,858
[MOTOYASU]
Damn it!

260
00:16:52,942 --> 00:16:54,858
Sir Motoyasu?
You can't be serious--

261
00:16:54,942 --> 00:16:56,608
you're not trying to
help the Shield?!

262
00:16:56,692 --> 00:16:58,567
[REN] Then why don't
you kill that thing?

263
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:02,358
[NAOFUMI grunts]

264
00:17:06,608 --> 00:17:08,733
[REN, MOTOYASU yell]

265
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,983
[yells]

266
00:17:15,358 --> 00:17:16,358
How was that?

267
00:17:16,442 --> 00:17:17,942
Got to admit, it was cool.

268
00:17:18,025 --> 00:17:20,317
But you're not doing
too much damage to it.

269
00:17:27,567 --> 00:17:29,275
[RAPHTALIA]
Master Naofumi...

270
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:40,400
[ZOMBIE DRAGON]
You will pay.

271
00:17:40,483 --> 00:17:43,442
Shut up. Just shut up!

272
00:17:43,525 --> 00:17:46,442
Come out, you coward!

273
00:17:46,525 --> 00:17:49,317
[ZOMBIE DRAGON]
I will make you pay!

274
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,442
I'll always believe in you.

275
00:17:59,525 --> 00:18:00,817
[gasps]

276
00:18:06,692 --> 00:18:11,192
[NAOFUMI] Didn't I swear
to protect Raphtalia, Filo,

277
00:18:11,275 --> 00:18:13,358
and all the villagers?!

278
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:36,525
Shield Prison!

279
00:18:48,233 --> 00:18:49,692
[NAOFUMI]
Not so fast!

280
00:18:49,775 --> 00:18:51,817
Time for Change Shield!

281
00:18:55,317 --> 00:18:57,275
[NAOFUMI, ZOMBIE DRAGON]
Within this virgin of cold ore,

282
00:18:57,358 --> 00:18:58,858
who shall swallow
even your screams

283
00:18:58,942 --> 00:19:00,775
with her embrace,
suffer in anguish

284
00:19:00,858 --> 00:19:03,858
as your entire body
is stabbed and skewered!

285
00:19:03,942 --> 00:19:06,233
I cast the Iron Maiden!

286
00:19:50,817 --> 00:19:52,942
Finally put an end to that...

287
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,567
[grunts]

288
00:19:59,150 --> 00:20:03,358
I don't, um... Master,
what just happened?

289
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:07,400
[RAPHTALIA]
Master Naofumi! Filo!

290
00:20:08,817 --> 00:20:10,358
[RAPHTALIA]
Are you all right?

291
00:20:10,442 --> 00:20:12,608
Why? Don't I look all right?

292
00:20:18,067 --> 00:20:19,317
[ITSUKI]
I'll be damned.

293
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,358
So that's what the
Shield's capable of.

294
00:20:22,442 --> 00:20:24,108
So basically, he cheated.

295
00:20:24,192 --> 00:20:26,817
You can bet things'll
be different next time!

296
00:20:28,025 --> 00:20:29,567
[FILO]
Hey...

297
00:20:29,650 --> 00:20:31,317
Don't tell me
you're a sore loser?

298
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,900
Th-That's not it, Filo.

299
00:20:32,983 --> 00:20:34,608
I'm, uh, just sayin'
I could easily

300
00:20:34,692 --> 00:20:36,942
have one-shotted that thing
if I'd gotten serious,

301
00:20:37,025 --> 00:20:39,067
you know what I mean?
It was a no brainer, really.

302
00:20:39,150 --> 00:20:40,358
Really?

303
00:20:40,442 --> 00:20:43,858
Um, oh, yeah, absolutely!
Motoyasu never lies.

304
00:20:43,942 --> 00:20:46,483
[FILO]
Then why didn't you?

305
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:48,108
Did you feel that?

306
00:20:53,775 --> 00:20:55,025
Another one?

307
00:20:55,108 --> 00:20:57,442
I've definitely never seen
this in the game before.

308
00:21:05,650 --> 00:21:06,817
[gasps]

309
00:21:08,317 --> 00:21:10,942
[GLASS]
How very disappointing.

310
00:21:22,733 --> 00:21:23,983
[GLASS]
You actually have trouble

311
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:26,483
with weaklings like these?

312
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:28,108
Are you really the heroes

313
00:21:28,192 --> 00:21:30,650
holding the world's
fate in their hands?

314
00:21:34,567 --> 00:21:38,233
There's only one here worthy
of being called a hero.

315
00:21:38,317 --> 00:21:40,442
And what is your name?

316
00:21:40,525 --> 00:21:44,192
How 'bout you introduce yourself
before asking someone's name.

317
00:21:44,275 --> 00:21:45,567
[GLASS]
Oh, pardon me.

318
00:21:45,650 --> 00:21:47,817
Whatever happened to my manners?

319
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:51,108
I am called Glass, and that's
all you need to know for now.

320
00:21:51,192 --> 00:21:53,900
Feel free to consider
me your enemy.

321
00:21:53,983 --> 00:21:55,358
Enemy?

322
00:21:56,358 --> 00:21:58,525
I'm Naofumi.

323
00:21:58,608 --> 00:22:00,025
[GLASS]
Naofumi.

324
00:22:00,108 --> 00:22:01,650
Well, well...

325
00:22:03,275 --> 00:22:04,608
[GLASS]
Then may I suggest...

326
00:22:04,692 --> 00:22:06,817
...that we begin...

327
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:10,067
...the only battle of this Wave
worthy of the name?

